CircuitMaker - Class in circuitikztool
Circuitmaker is an extension of JPanel which allows for the user to draw schematics using the components supplied by the Components class in this project. uses mouse input to draw components with the selected component.
CircuitMaker() - Constructor for class circuitikztool.CircuitMaker
CircuitMaker constructor, initializes the components ArrayList and attaches input listeners to the current window.
clearSchematic() - Method in class circuitikztool.CircuitMaker
Erases all placed components, clears LaTeX String and Components list
Component - Class in circuitikztool
Component is meant to be a data object for storing all possible component objects in a single arrayList inside of the class CircuitMaker.
Component(int) - Constructor for class circuitikztool.Component
Constructor for component as an option.
Component(Point2D, int) - Constructor for class circuitikztool.Component
Constructor for NON-PATH components, requires only a position and a selected component value. consult the constants at the top of the class for valid input values to this function
Component(Point2D, Point2D, int) - Constructor for class circuitikztool.Component
